31/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A close associate of alleged drug trafficker Darko Saric was killed on Sunday (May 30th) in the town of Kotor. 
Dragan Dudic, aka "Fric", was shot outside a local bar and died in hospital. 
Police arrested a 32-year-old man in relation to the attack. 
According to the media, Dudic was involved in money laundering from cocaine deals. 
Serbia wants to arrest Saric in connection with the smuggling of 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America. 
He is still at large. 
Saric's gang is believed to be one of the top organised crime groups in the Balkans. 
(RTCG, RTS, PC Nen - 30/05/10)
